10/19 Younger people are natural app adopters, but may not fear the illness that much or see the point. People from poorer backgrounds - who may be particularly vulnerable to the effects of Covid - may be less likely to have smartphones. Older folk may feel excluded.

8/19 I can only be alerted to the fact I've encountered someone positive for Covid if I have the app *and* they have the app. So the whole system hinges on widespread adoption. A figure of 60% has been mooted. (Strangely, this is the same as the suggested herd immunity number.)
